import heapq

def minPath(grid, k):
    n = len(grid)
    
    min_heap = [(grid[0][0], 0, 0, [grid[0][0]])]  # Modified to include the full path taken
    seen = set((0, 0))  # Only include the coordinates in the seen set
    
    path = []
    while min_heap:
        val, i, j, curr_path = heapq.heappop(min_heap)
        path = curr_path
        
        if len(path) == k:  # Stop when the required number of steps is reached
            break
        
        for x, y in [(i+1, j), (i, j+1)]:
            if 0 <= x < n and 0 <= y < n and (x, y) not in seen:  # Include only coordinates in seen set
                heapq.heappush(min_heap, (grid[x][y], x, y, curr_path + [grid[x][y]]))
                seen.add((x, y))
    
    return path
